<darkcolour>A6416E</darkcolour><section><title>&lt;I&gt;A/an, some&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;any&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;a/an&lt;/I&gt; before singular countable nouns when there is only one.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_4_2_1.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_4_2_2.mp3</sound1><text1a>I have &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; TV but I don't have &lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt; mobile phone.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_4_2_3.mp3</sound2><text2a>Do you have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;a&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; car?</text2a><titlesound2>ELEMGRAM_4_2_4.mp3</titlesound2><sectiontitle2>Use &lt;I&gt;some&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;any&lt;/I&gt; when the number isn't important. We usually use &lt;I&gt;some&lt;/I&gt; in affirmatives, and &lt;I&gt;any&lt;/I&gt; in negatives and questions.</sectiontitle2><text3>%undefined</text3><sound3>ELEMGRAM_4_2_5.mp3</sound3><text3a>We have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;some&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; magazines but we don't have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;any&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; books.</text3a><text4>%undefined</text4><sound4>ELEMGRAM_4_2_6.mp3</sound4><text4a>Do you have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;any&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; dictionaries?</text4a></section><section><title>&lt;I&gt;A/an, some&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;any&lt;/I&gt;</title><sectiontitle>Use &lt;I&gt;some&lt;/I&gt; and &lt;I&gt;any&lt;/I&gt; with uncountable nouns and plural countable nouns.</sectiontitle><titlesound>ELEMGRAM_4_2_7.mp3</titlesound><text1></text1><sound1>ELEMGRAM_4_2_8.mp3</sound1><text1a>I have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;some rice&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; and &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;some eggs&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;.</text1a><text2></text2><sound2>ELEMGRAM_4_2_9.mp3</sound2><text2a>Do you have &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;any rice&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt; or &lt;B&gt;&lt;Font color='#A6416E'&gt;any eggs&lt;/Font&gt;&lt;/B&gt;?</text2a><ti